###Setting up a proportion

Corresponding sides of similar triangles are proportional, so we can set up and solve a proportion:

$\dfrac{\blueE{PA}}{BO}=\dfrac{\tealE{OA}}{\maroonD{RO}}$

We picked side $\blueE{\overline{PA}}$ because we need to find its length.

We picked side $\overline{BO}$ because it corresponds to side $\blueE{\overline{PA}}$.

Then we picked another pair of corresponding sides where we already knew the measurements.

$\begin{array}{rcl}
&\triangle PAO
\\
{\text{long} \atop \text{leg}}
&\overbrace{\underbrace{\!\!\!\!\!\left\{ 
\dfrac{\blueE{PA}}{BO}=\dfrac{\tealE{OA}}{\maroonD{RO}}
\right\}\!\!\!\!\!}}
&{\scriptsize{\text{hypotenuse}}}
\\
&\triangle BOR
\end{array}$
